## ğŸš€ 100 Days of AWS Cloud Journey

Today I learned how to **launch an EC2 (Elastic Compute Cloud) instance** in AWS and understood the core components like AMI, instance type, key pair, security groups, and networking.

---

## ğŸ”¹ What is an EC2 Instance?

An **EC2 instance** is a **virtual server in the AWS cloud** used to run applications, websites, and services with full control over the operating system.

---

## ğŸ› ï¸ Step-by-Step: Create an EC2 Instance

---

## 1ï¸âƒ£ Login to AWS Console

* Go to **[https://aws.amazon.com](https://aws.amazon.com)**
* Sign in to **AWS Management Console**
* Select your **Region** (example: `ap-south-1`)

---

## 2ï¸âƒ£ Open EC2 Dashboard

* Search for **EC2**
* Click **EC2 â†’ Instances**
* Click **Launch instance**

---

## 3ï¸âƒ£ Choose an Amazon Machine Image (AMI)

An **AMI** defines the operating system.

Common choices:

* Amazon Linux 2023 (Recommended)
* Ubuntu 22.04 LTS
* Red Hat / Windows

ğŸ‘‰ Select **Amazon Linux** and click **Select**

---

## 4ï¸âƒ£ Choose Instance Type

This defines CPU and RAM.

| Instance Type | Use Case            |
| ------------- | ------------------- |
| t2.micro      | Free Tier, practice |
| t3.micro      | Better performance  |
| t3.small      | Small apps          |

ğŸ‘‰ Choose **t2.micro** (Free Tier)
ğŸ‘‰ Click **Next / Continue**

---

## 5ï¸âƒ£ Configure Key Pair (Login Access)

* Click **Create new key pair**
* Name: `ec2-key`
* Type: **RSA**
* Format: **.pem**
* Download and store safely

ğŸ“Œ Required for SSH access

---

## 6ï¸âƒ£ Configure Network Settings

* VPC: Default VPC (or custom)
* Subnet: Public subnet
* Auto-assign Public IP: **Enable**

---

## 7ï¸âƒ£ Configure Security Group (Firewall)

### Create new security group

| Type  | Port | Source    |
| ----- | ---- | --------- |
| SSH   | 22   | My IP     |
| HTTP  | 80   | 0.0.0.0/0 |
| HTTPS | 443  | 0.0.0.0/0 |

ğŸ“Œ Security groups control **inbound traffic**

---

## 8ï¸âƒ£ Configure Storage

* Root volume: **gp3**
* Size: 8â€“20 GiB (Free Tier)

gp3 is recommended for:
âœ” Lower cost
âœ” Better performance

---

## 9ï¸âƒ£ Add Tags (Best Practice)

* Key: `Name`
* Value: `My-First-EC2`

Tags help with:

* Resource management
* Cost tracking

---

## ğŸ”Ÿ Review & Launch

* Review all configurations
* Click **Launch instance**

Instance state will change:

```
Pending â†’ Running
```

---

## ğŸ”‘ Step-by-Step: Connect to EC2 via SSH

### 1ï¸âƒ£ Set Permissions (Linux/Mac)

```bash
chmod 400 ec2-key.pem
```

---

### 2ï¸âƒ£ Connect to Instance

```bash
ssh -i ec2-key.pem ec2-user@<public-ip>
```

For Ubuntu:

```bash
ssh -i ec2-key.pem ubuntu@<public-ip>
```

---

## âœ… Verify Instance

```bash
whoami
```

Output:

```
ec2-user
```

ğŸ‰ Successfully connected!

